comment: Lemma for ~ line2y . This proof is based on counterexamples for the following cases: 1. ` C =/= 0 ` : p = (0,0) (LHS of bicondional is false, RHS is true); 2. ` C = 0 /\ B =/= 0 ` : p = (1,-A/B) (LHS of bicondional is true, RHS is false); 3. ` A = B = C = 0 ` : p = (1,1) (LHS of bicondional is true, RHS is false). (Contributed by AV, 4-Feb-2023.)
